{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_chrysocolla_ver01/data/sn89070012/00517019549/1949060201/1085.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE TWO\nV6Q\u00a3 NOT SO Dum^\nEL DUMBO\nOld Si Whiff.c .ee. who comes\ninto town a couple cf mes a year\nfrom his home out in (he Cherry\ncow's, was in the fTst of the week\nto stock up on eatin\u2019 tobacker and\nother necessities of life, and to\nget the news, if any. He has no\nradio, no neighbors and never\nreads the newspapers, and so nat\nurally he gets quite a fur piece\nbehind on the news.\nLast time he was in town was\na week or so before the election\nlast fall; didn\u2019t have no curiosity\nabout how the election came out\nfor like he says, \u201cIt don\u2019t make\nno difference who\u2019s elected.\nThey're all alike, them politicians,\nand it don\u2019t make no never mind\nto me who the president is. They\ndon\u2019t none of \u2019em ever do any\nthing for me.\u201d\nBut when he heard about the\nmines laying off men and heard\nthe squawks of the business men\nabout the depression or recession,\nhe k\u2019nda peked up and said,\n\"Well. President Truman told you\nlast fall what would happen when\nyou elected ^ewey. He said the\nRepublicans would stick a knife\nin your back, and he said that he\nwas the frien of the workingman\nand they\u2019d hotter elect him for\nthe Republicans would give \u2019em\nthe worst of it. He told you that\nif he got in he\u2019d repeal the Labor\nLaw and he\u2019d give you a good one\nin its place. He told you things\nwouldn't be so good if Dewey got\nin but you went ahead and elected\nhim and give the Republicans an\nother chance, and now ain\u2019t you\nsorry you didn\u2019t listen to him:\nlook where you are now.\u201d\n\u201cBut. Si.\u201d said the bartender in\nthe place where he was spouting\noff. \"Dewey wasn't elected and\nTruman was and he\u2019s still presi-\nmA i\naS\nBBHBBup^^bh^.\u2019\nLloyd Nolan jn \u201cPier 13\u201d with\nLynn Bari at the Lyric Friday and\nSaturday.\n_ Estimate Cost of Atlantic Pact _____\nOf >BmB\nM BHU v *hBBM\naMi i X'\nraa Ms \u25a0Waa\nibMbbMw\u00df b\u00dfb\u00dfPb^\nWASHINGTON, D. C.\u2014Secretary of State Acheson and Defense Secretary Johnson met with the\nSenate Foreign Relations Committee to give their estimate of the cost of the Atlantic Pact in dollars\n\u2022nd arms. Left to right: Chairman Tom Connally of Texas, of the Senate Foreign Relations Com\nmittee; W. Averell Harriman, Marshall Plan \u201croving\" ambassador, who also sat in on the closed-door\nmeeting; Defense Secretary Louis Johnson; Secretary of State Dean Acheson, and committee member,\nWalter F. George of Georgia. t\ndent, and pretty near all the Dem\nocrats were elected. Didn\u2019t you\nknow that?\u201d\n\u201cNo, I ain\u2019t been in town since\nlast October,\u201d said the Old Man\nof the Mountain. \u201cI never heared\nwho was elected, but I sure\nthought from the way things was\nlookin\u2019 that Dewey musta got in\njust like everybody thought he\nwould. Gosh. Truman said, last\nthat I heared, that if they put\nhim back in that everything would\nbe hunky dory. Are you sure that\nit wasn\u2019t Dewey that got in?\u201d\nAssured that he had heard right\nthe first time the old man went\nout shaking his head.\n\u201cJust can\u2019t figger it, I just .can\u2019t\nfigger\u2019 it,\u201d he said. \u201cEverything\nturned out just like Truman said\nit would if he got beat. Guess I\nhad better beat it back to the\nCherrycows, where you don\u2019t hear\nnothin', don\u2019t know nothin\u2019 and\ndon\u2019t give a damn.\u201d\nHAMILTON SEZ\nLong Skirts are like Prohibition\nthe joints are still there but\nthey are harder to spot.\nJust when and if\u2014are the ladies\ngoing to make up \"our\u201d minds on\nthe long and short of the skirt\nissue?\nLong skirts have advantages\nsome say that the girls in long\nskirts stay married to the same\nman longer if that is any ad\nvantage.\nOn the other hand short skirts\nhave advantages. Girls and old\nmaids in short skirts move off the/\nmarket faster.\nAfter you are married most\nhusbands prefer that you wear\nyour skirts longer. Yes, about 3\nyears longer.\nAlso for ladies with small chil\ndren. longer skirts that reach\ndown to where the babies can\nreach up and grab them tends\nto keep the family group collect\ned and more centrally located, at\ntimes.\nWhile short skirts are always\npreferred by occulists and eye\nglass fitters as they increase\nthe trade.\nA mother in a short skirt\nwith a grown daughter in a long\nskirt is definitely confusing except\nat night clubs and churches and\nshould be stopped.\nLong skirts do cover up the\nbow in bow legs and the\nknock in knock knees.\nShort skirts cover up otherwise\nwasted beauty, and charm.\nLong skirts create a shortage\nin the world market of cotton,\nsilks, wool and whistles \u201cat.\u201d\nShort skirts cause eye-strain\nand alimony.\nA beautiful woman in a full\nflowing long skirt is a gift from\nthe Gods.\nBut a voluptuous blond in a\ntight waist and a short skirt is a\nbit of heaven itself.\nGAZETTE by mail $2.50 a year.\nBREWERY GULCH GAZETTE\nPlay Suitl\nf \u2019MM\nB I gill\nKm r I' 1 IB\n'till\n4 BBl^^\nIMHi. I BHlliillw\nMADISON, WIS. Attractive\nstole and strapless bra are 1949\nfashion features of this versatile\nvacation ensemble, modeled in Wis\nconsin\u2019s beautiful Cave of the\nMounds. Carefree outfit, in tropical\n\u00a3rint cotton, includes flared skirt\nJ addition to trim shorts shown.\nCave of the Mounds, discovered 10\nyears ago this summer, is on U.S.\n'highways 18 and 151, 25 miles west\nof here.\n7^^\u201c\n|1 Ri\niOB\u00ae WK\nWHAT OF TOMORROW,\nLITTLE MAN?\nBy Jack Benjamin\nThere are certain thinkers who,\ninvariably, stimulate us. Even\nthough we may not agree with\ntheir tenets, our thoughts are\nusually different after reading\nthem. For instance a rereading of\nNietzsche always leads one to new\navenues of reflection. Recently,\nwe had occasion to dip into his\nwell-known \u201cThus Spake Zara\nthustra\u201d and \u201cGeanology of Mor\nals.\u201d This led us to ponder the\nproblems of a revaluation of all\nvalues, as he so well put it.\nIt might not be a bad idea to\nchallenge our beliefs every now\nand then so we can find out what\nbarnacles we carry around. If the\nbelief is valid and logical it can\nwithstand criticism; if it isn\u2019t, it\nshould be thrown off promptly,\nwithout any further ado.\nMankind, no doubt, would find\niconoclasm somewhat beneficial,\nespecially in our present age. The\nwhole, sad history of Man is one\nlong, sorry tale of insane butch\nery. For every step' that lie took\nforward, he left behind wrack and\nruin. And. it wasn\u2019t really a step\nforward, it was a stumble, pro\npelled by the forces behind him.\nIt takes a war to bring about im\nprovements and inventions in\ndaily life. Only in a war does Man\nthrow himself into a frenzy to\ndiscover new and better means of\nexterminating his fellow-man.\nThe discoveries which he can\u2019t\nuse along that line he throws back\ninto civil life. Ah, but, in peace\nful life we don\u2019t find that mad\nness to investigate. Human life is\ncheap.\nHe hates to have his short\ncomings brought to his attention\nand, therefore, listens with rapt\near to the soft-spoken flatterer of\nthe market-place. With anger he\nturns from criticism that marks\nhis brutality, his utter lack of uni\nversal decency and his bovine but\nwolfish propensities. Whatever\nprogress has accrued came about\nmainly by sheer chance. With but\nshort and fleeting pauses, warfare\nmarks his existence. Looking at\nthe problem from a world-wide\npoint of view, Man is ethically\nCREATED BY LIBERTYVILLE TEXTILES*\nGS\ngive your room\na Modern flair\nThey\u2019re MODERN yet at home with any\nperiod style. Tumble-Twist rugs give even\nthe colonial room a certain modern flair\u2014\nW an up-to-dateness. Use them wherever a\nroom needs a new note; see what wonders\nof rejuvenation they perform. Available in\nall colors. Thick, soft, luxurious and\nlasting.\nExclusive alt-woven \u201cstagger-weave\"\nr I construction\nLoop twisted fine cotton boucle yarns\nPre^ shrunk, color- fast; improve with\nlaundering\nOf American materials; by American\n''craftsmen\nSize 24x48 in.\nSize 27x54 in.\n$|Q95\nSize 36x60 in.\n*l4*\nNon-Skid Rug Anchor Free With Each\nTumble-Twist Rug\nFURNITURE DEPT.\nBISBEE, ARIZONA, THURSDAY, JUNE 2, 1949\nbankrupt. In fact, we shouldn\u2019t\nsay \u201cbankrupt\u201d because he never\nreally accumulated any ethical\ncapital.\nFor the overwhelming majority,\nthe satisfaction of their basic, ani\nmal desires is sufficient. Give\nthem food, drink, shelter and\nsome oafish amusement and they\nremain in petrified^ contentment.\nThinking they avoid as one avoids\na plague. Only under the direst\ncompulsion do they even make a\nslight effort in that direction, and\nthat effort is generally made\nwhen the stomach is vacant for a\nlonger time than it is usually ac\ncustomed to be so. And when a\nmass of bamboozled beings at\ntempt to think along lines of care\nful and intelligent direction, the\nB^^r B\n\nTeresa Wright in \u201cEnchant\nment\u201d with David Niven at the\nLowell Thursday thru Sunday.","height":"19404","width":"12936"}}
